                     <p>West-Haddon.

   <persName>Sir <forename>Eustace</forename>, lord of <placeName role="lord" type="manor" key="place_108156">Watford</placeName>, kt.</persName>, grants to <orgName key="org_108004">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </orgName> in free alms the whole of a tenement in <placeName key="place_108032">West Haddon</placeName>, which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, vicar of <placeName role="vicar" key="place_108032">W<supplied>est</supplied> H<supplied>addon</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName>, sometime held of him.
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Eustace</forename> 
                           <surname>Golafre</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108142">Watford</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> son of <persName>
                              <forename>Peter</forename> of <surname>Holm</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> son of <surname>William</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> son of <surname>Herbert</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> the <surname>clerk</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> le <surname>freman</surname>
                        </persName>,
   <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">son of Simon</surname>
                        </persName>.<!--<note type="foot" n="1">The witnesses are the same as in N’hants. ch. 3 (above), and it is in the same hand.</note>--> 
   <origDate notBefore="1220" notAfter="1230" precision="low">
                           <supplied>c. 1220–30.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
